42290: /*
42290:  * Test icon URI functionality
42290:  *
42290:  */
42290: 
42290: const Ci = Components.interfaces;
42290: const Cc = Components.classes;
42290: 
42290: // There are 3 types of valid icon URIs:
42290: // 1. moz-icon:[valid URL]
42290: // 2. moz-icon://[file name]
42290: // 3. moz-icon://stock/[icon identifier]
43725: // Plus we also support moz-icon://[valid URL] for backwards compatibility.
42290: 
42290: // Main test entry point.
42290: function run_test() {
42290:   let ioService = Cc["@mozilla.org/network/io-service;1"].getService(Ci.nsIIOService);
42290:   let currentSpec = ""; // the uri spec that we're currently testing
42290:   let exception = false; // whether or not an exception was thrown
42290:   let uri = null; // the current URI
42290:   let iconURI = null; // the current icon URI
42290: 
42290:   // Note that if the scheme is not correct the ioservice won't even create an icon URI
42290:   // so don't bother testing incorrect schemes here.
42290: 
42290:   // Make sure a valid file name icon URI can be created and that we can obtain
42290:   // all arguments, the spec, and the file extension.
42290:   currentSpec = "moz-icon://foo.html?contentType=bar&size=button&state=normal";
42290:   try {
42290:     uri = ioService.newURI(currentSpec, null, null);
42290:   } catch (e) {
42290:     exception = true;
42290:   }
42290:   do_check_eq(exception, false);
42290:   exception = false; // reset exception value
42290: 
42290:   iconURI = uri.QueryInterface(Ci.nsIMozIconURI);
42290:   do_check_eq(iconURI.iconSize, "button");
42290:   do_check_eq(iconURI.iconState, "normal");
42290:   do_check_eq(iconURI.contentType, "bar");
42290:   do_check_eq(iconURI.fileExtension, ".html");
42290: 
42290:   // Make sure a valid file name icon URI can be created with a numeric size,
42290:   // and make sure the numeric size is handled properly
42290:   currentSpec = "moz-icon://foo.html?size=3";
42290:   try {
42290:     uri = ioService.newURI(currentSpec, null, null);
42290:   } catch (e) {
42290:     exception = true;
42290:   }
42290:   do_check_eq(exception, false);
42290:   exception = false; // reset exception value
42290: 
42290:   iconURI = uri.QueryInterface(Ci.nsIMozIconURI);
42290:   do_check_eq(iconURI.iconSize, "");
42290:   do_check_eq(iconURI.imageSize, 3);
42290: 
42290:   // Make sure a valid stock icon URI can be created and that we can obtain
42290:   // the stock icon's name.
42290:   currentSpec = "moz-icon://stock/foo";
42290:   try {
42290:     uri = ioService.newURI(currentSpec, null, null);
42290:   } catch (e) {
42290:     exception = true;
42290:   }
42290:   do_check_eq(exception, false);
42290:   exception = false; // reset exception value
42290: 
42290:   iconURI = uri.QueryInterface(Ci.nsIMozIconURI);
42290:   do_check_eq(iconURI.stockIcon, "foo");
42290: 
67586:   // Make sure an invalid stock icon URI, missing icon identifier, throws.
67586:   currentSpec = "moz-icon://stock/?size=3";
67586:   try {
67586:     uri = ioService.newURI(currentSpec, null, null);
67586:   } catch (e) {
67586:     exception = true;
67586:   }
67586:   do_check_true(exception);
67586:   exception = false; // reset exception value
67586: 
42290:   // Make sure a valid file URL icon URI can be created and that we can obtain
42290:   // the URL and QI it to an nsIFileURL.
42290:   currentSpec = "moz-icon:file://foo.txt";
42290:   try {
42290:     uri = ioService.newURI(currentSpec, null, null);
42290:   } catch (e) {
42290:     exception = true;
42290:   }
42290:   do_check_eq(exception, false);
42290:   exception = false; // reset exception value
42290: 
42290:   iconURI = uri.QueryInterface(Ci.nsIMozIconURI);
42290:   let fileURL = null;
42290:   try {
42290:     fileURL = iconURI.iconURL.QueryInterface(Ci.nsIFileURL);
42290:   } catch (e) {
42290:     exception = true;
42290:   }
42290:   do_check_eq(exception, false);
42290:   exception = false; // reset exception value
42290: 
43725:   do_check_neq(fileURL, null);
43725: 
43725:   // Now test a file URI which has been created with an extra //
43725:   currentSpec = "moz-icon://file://foo.txt";
43725:   try {
43725:     uri = ioService.newURI(currentSpec, null, null);
43725:   } catch (e) {
43725:     exception = true;
43725:   }
43725:   do_check_eq(exception, false);
43725:   exception = false; // reset exception value
43725: 
43725:   iconURI = uri.QueryInterface(Ci.nsIMozIconURI);
43725:   let fileURL = null;
43725:   try {
43725:     fileURL = iconURI.iconURL.QueryInterface(Ci.nsIFileURL);
43725:   } catch (e) {
43725:     exception = true;
43725:   }
43725:   do_check_eq(exception, false);
43725:   exception = false; // reset exception value
43725: 
43725:   do_check_neq(fileURL, null);
42290: 
42290:   // Now test a simple invalid icon URI. This should fail.
42290:   currentSpec = "moz-icon:foo";
42290:   try {
42290:     uri = ioService.newURI(currentSpec, null, null);
42290:   } catch (e) {
42290:     exception = true;
42290:   }
42290:   do_check_eq(exception, true);
42290:   exception = false; // reset exception value
42290: 
42290:   // Now test an icon URI that has a URI for a path but that is not a URL. This should fail.
42290:   // This is png data for a little red dot that I got from wikipedia.
42290:   currentSpec = "moz-icon:data:image/png;base64,";
42290:   try {
42290:     uri = ioService.newURI(currentSpec, null, null);
42290:   } catch (e) {
42290:     exception = true;
42290:   }
42290:   do_check_eq(exception, true);
42290:   exception = false; // reset exception value
42290: 
42290:   // Now test a URI that should be a file name but is ridiculously long. This should fail.
42290:   currentSpec = "moz-icon://data:application/vnd.ms-excel;base64,";
42290:   try {
42290:     uri = ioService.newURI(currentSpec, null, null);
42290:   } catch (e) {
42290:     exception = true;
42290:   }
42290:   do_check_eq(exception, true);
42290:   exception = false; // reset exception value
42290: };
